ENTRY       EC 1.14.13.173              Enzyme
NAME        11-oxo-beta-amyrin 30-oxidase;
            CYP72A;
            CYP72A154
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen;
            With NADH or NADPH as one donor, and incorporation of one atom of oxygen into the other donor
SYSNAME     11-oxo-beta-amyrin,NADPH:oxygen oxidoreductase (30-hydroxylating)
REACTION    11-oxo-beta-amyrin + 3 O2 + 3 NADPH + 3 H+ = glycyrrhetinate + 3 NADP+ + 4 H2O (overall reaction) [RN:R10316];
            (1a) 11-oxo-beta-amyrin + O2 + NADPH + H+ = 30-hydroxy-11-oxo-beta-amyrin + NADP+ + H2O [RN:R10313];
            (1b) 30-hydroxy-11-oxo-beta-amyrin + O2 + NADPH + H+ = glycyrrhetaldehyde + NADP+ + 2 H2O [RN:R10314];
            (1c) glycyrrhetaldehyde + O2 + NADPH + H+ = glycyrrhetinate + NADP+ + H2O [RN:R10315]
ALL_REAC    R10313 R10314 R10315 R10316
SUBSTRATE   11-oxo-beta-amyrin [CPD:C19943];
            O2 [CPD:C00007];
            NADPH [CPD:C00005];
            H+ [CPD:C00080];
            30-hydroxy-11-oxo-beta-amyrin [CPD:C20510];
            glycyrrhetaldehyde [CPD:C20511]
PRODUCT     glycyrrhetinate [CPD:C02283];
            NADP+ [CPD:C00006];
            H2O [CPD:C00001];
            30-hydroxy-11-oxo-beta-amyrin [CPD:C20510];
            glycyrrhetaldehyde [CPD:C20511]
COMMENT     A heme-thiolate protein (cytochrome P-450). The enzyme is involved in the biosynthesis of the triterpenoid saponin glycyrrhizin in the plant Glycyrrhiza uralensis (licorice). The enzyme from the plant Medicago truncatula can also hydroxylate beta-amyrin.
